<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-7C94B26D-6B6D-4709-813E-5847113796B5" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-7C94B26D-6B6D-4709-813E-5847113796B5" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">01 How to do the basic adjustment of the curing carriage</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-173AF84C-D126-4DD5-8ABA-ADD08113B9D4"><p class="- topic/p ">With this adjustment you do the basic adjustment of the curing carriage on the frame. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Adjustment</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_A392D23B9FA5434A8095E72A33F001E1" class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">2 x distance strip 12 mm (part of modification 02) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to adjust</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Loosen the 2 screws [A]. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5F734FFF-3EFE-48E2-AD53-DB955247BE6F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CCB419A2-83DE-4A00-9AC4-15ED4E63BE15-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CCB419A2-83DE-4A00-9AC4-15ED4E63BE15-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Push the complete curing guidance to the rear side of the printer (as indicated with the arrow in the drawing). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Lock the 2 screws [A]. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-6DA9FF1A-94B1-4CF2-8F99-1581DBE7B7F9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D9700989-5028-4AF1-950A-648069AF2AE5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D9700989-5028-4AF1-950A-648069AF2AE5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Position the curing carriage in the middle of the platen (no cover / no curing mirror). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-31937B7D-B284-4E1F-8447-12D35A7DC2B1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-346AE0B9-0842-45DC-9610-4239F6CDEB70-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-346AE0B9-0842-45DC-9610-4239F6CDEB70-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the mirror at the left and right hand side of the curing carriage.
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 4 screws at the left and right hand side of the curing carriage.
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7F9F1D11-DEED-4650-8FCE-D08300DA90EC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E96EB7B8-6211-4AA2-B9A8-DF60A95009A9-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E96EB7B8-6211-4AA2-B9A8-DF60A95009A9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Loosen the 2 screws [A] and 4 screws [B] at the left and right hand side of the curing carriage. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-715636BA-EF09-4B73-83DB-20FC6382318E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7B26C8CE-6B28-4CA8-B927-FC56BB6E4636-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7B26C8CE-6B28-4CA8-B927-FC56BB6E4636-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the distance strip on the platen at the left and right hand side of the frame [F] of the curing unit. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the frame [F] touches the distance strip at position 1, 2, 3,and 4. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The distance = 12 +/- 0.5 mm. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-DAC3901C-8D0D-4DF6-82C8-1F04FD66D7CB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-15AEB85D-215B-42E9-A49F-B38B74AF889C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-15AEB85D-215B-42E9-A49F-B38B74AF889C-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-C9815569-FC53-454C-BF61-2991D9583CCC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-81328C77-2559-4726-823D-C8034DBCAE55-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-81328C77-2559-4726-823D-C8034DBCAE55-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Push the curing carriage to the rear side of the printer. 
</p><note id="GUID-4CCC1D21-31BA-4691-8198-386D7CB5AC6C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the plate touches the distance tool by it's own weight. 
</p></note></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tighten the 2 screws [A] at the left and right hand side. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tighten the 4 screws [B] at the left and right hand side. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-1966D88E-E49F-4681-A876-69CD7F90736E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5FDC1BC3-4A48-42CF-A4E5-0CD869829541-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5FDC1BC3-4A48-42CF-A4E5-0CD869829541-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-1F897B6A-3B52-4EA1-AC18-9626A9B429D4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Adjustment</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
